The paper deals with strategic voting in a preference elicitation process, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also proposes a practical algorithm for strategic voting, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The empirical study conducted in the paper involves statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
